---
import { withBase } from '../../lib/url';
import Prose from '../../layouts/Prose.astro';
import GerardCastingWidget from '../../components/course/GerardCastingWidget.astro';
import { TOOLS } from '../../lib/tools';

const tool = TOOLS.find((t) => t.slug === 'astronomical-casting')!;
---

<Prose
  title={tool.title}
  description={tool.description}
  crumbs={[{ name: 'Tools', href: '/tools/' }, { name: tool.title }]}
  kicker="Practice Tools"
>
  <p>
    Geomancy has a second, older branch: the <em>astronomical geomancy</em> of Gerard of Cremona,
    in which the figures do not fill a shield at all. One cast figure puts a zodiac sign on the
    Ascendant; the signs follow in order through a square chart of twelve houses; and nine
    further casts of points place the planets, each by the remainder of its points divided by
    twelve. The chart is then judged as an astrologer judges (by lords, planets and signs) with
    no Witnesses and no Judge anywhere in it.
  </p>
  <p>
    This tool erects the whole figure, at once or step by step with every count, sum and
    remainder shown. The method is taught whole in
    <a href={withBase('/course/astrological-geomancy/')}>Lesson 12</a>, and the medieval treatise itself
    (in Robert Turner's 1655 translation) is in
    <a href={withBase('/library/gerard/introduction/')}>the library</a>, short enough to read in an evening
    and the best companion this tool can have.
  </p>

  <GerardCastingWidget />
</Prose>
